* Save Structured (JSON) Results with Runner Status (LPT) to RaceRoster.
*
*   When to use:    During LPT-enabled races to publish results with runner status.
*   How to use:     Double-click to upload structured results including runner status.
*
*   Note:           LPT requires structured (JSON) results — unstructured (text) uploads
*                   are not supported by Live Predictive Tracking.
*
*   Setup:
*     Pass the RaceRoster sub-event ID below.
*     Example (direct):  ResultsOnlineLPT.rsm   297655
*     Example (Entries): ResultsOnlineLPT.rsm   %rr_5k%
*
*   Recommendation:
*     - Run @CalcStatus.lst first so RUNNER STATUS is populated before upload.
*     - Use a dedicated sub-event ID for LPT (e.g. %rr_5k%) defined in Entries.INI.
*     - Timer must choose either LPT or non-LPT workflow for the race — do not mix
*       @AutoResults and @AutoResultsLPT on the same sub-event.

ResultsOnlineLPT.rsm   %rr_5k%
